, Pauli-Fierz 1939). The\nPutnam-Gr\\\"unbaum debate on conventionality is revisited given a broad modal\nscope. Massive scalar gravity licenses a historically plausible rational\nreconstruction of much of space-time philosophy in light of particle physics.\nAn appendix reconsiders the Malament-Weatherall-Manchak conformal restriction\nof conventionality and constructs the `universal force' in the null cones.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 Sep 2015 11:46:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-21"}
